                  <msItem>
                     <p> KINGESDON. <persName>
                           <forename>Michael</forename>, son of <persName>
                              <forename>Arnulf</forename> de <surname>Kingesdon</surname>
                           </persName>
                        </persName>, 
                  grants to <pb n="99"/> 
                        <persName>
                           <forename>Ralph</forename> de  <surname>Chimbeham</surname>
                        </persName> 
                  a rent of 21 1/2d. which <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Joseph</surname>
                        </persName> 
                  was accustomed annually to pay to him for land which lies between the field called
                  <placeName type="minor">Northfeld</placeName> and the land of
                  <persName>
                           <forename>William</forename> 
                           <surname>Clodham</surname>
                        </persName>'s; also 5d.
                  annual rent in the same village which 
                  <persName nymRef="Brankeshecche">
                           <forename>William</forename>, son of <persName>
                              <forename>Felicia</forename> de <surname>Brankeshecche</surname>
                           </persName>
                        </persName>, 
                  paid at an annual rent of one halfpenny for all services
                  and demands. For this grant the said Ralph gave 16s. sterling.
                  (<origDate notBefore="1250" notAfter="1260" precision="low">c. 1250-60</origDate>.)
                  
               </p>
